The imperial bastards have us in a tight spot. But with a little luck and Talos to guide us, we shall prevail.
Currently we have the upper hand.
Praise Talos, we have the advantage here. And we'll use it to press those faithless imperial dogs into submission.
Currently we are about even strength. We aim to change that soldier.

Cell.Text: First off, we've learned the location of some rebel scouts. Need to take them out.
First off, there's a couple of imperials skulking about spying on our movements. Need to cut their throats so they can't make their reports.
First off, the got some rebels holed up in a nearby settlement. Need to clean them out so our boys can move in.
First off, there's a band of imperials hiding in a nearby village. We're gonna flush them out and put them to the sword.
First, we need to limit the capability and prestige of the Stormcloaks by sabotaging an important resource they claim to control.
First problem here is a pack of imperial dogs drooling over resources stolen from the people. A little sabotage will sour the taste of that victory.
We have information regarding the movements of a rebel courier. We need to intercept him and confiscate his package.
First, we've learnt the whereabouts of an imperial cur fetching documents for his master in Solitude. We need to put a muzzle on that, don't we?
First of all, one of our men was captured by rebels who refuse to surrender him. So we're going to break him out.
First of all, a Son of Skyrim rots in an imperial prison. We'll be getting him out of there soon.
First of all, I want to sew confusion and doubt through the rebel troops. I need someone to assassinate their commanding officer.
First, we should kill their field commander. And we'll strike them while they're busy tucking their tails between their legs.
First, our intelligence suggests one of the rebel garrisons has become disaffected. If we play our cards right, we should be able to turn them.
First off, we hear a group of imperial legions are coming around to our way of thinking. With the right kind of encouragement they'll join our side.
First off, seems the Jarl's Steward might be vulnerable to blackmail. Need someone to investigate that possibility.
First off, it seems that we might be able to blackmail the Jarl's Steward. I need someone to find out for sure.
First on my list, is a problem with our supply caravans being constantly attacked by a giant. A giant! Need someone to care of that soon.
The last few supply caravans have been attacked... by a giant. That's right, one those big hairy brutes. As if I didn't have enough to deal with.
First, I need to get a handle on rebel operations. I need someone to discretely liberate some documents from their headquarters.
First, I need to know what the imperials are planning. Need someone to slip into their headquarters, grab plans, maps, something useful like that.
First of all, I'd like to drum up some more support from the local populace. I have someone in mind I'd like you to have a chat with.
First of all, there's someone in particular I'd like to win over to our cause. Need someone to drop in over there and have a little chat.
First off, there's an Orc hanging around causing me headaches. Something about a vision quest he needs help with.
First off, there's a damn Orc hanging around getting in the way. He's been yammering on about needing help with some kind of vision quest.

Cell.Text: [S] Secondly, some rebel scouts passed through that have seen too much. Need to take them out before they report back to their leaders.
[S] Secondly, we got a couple of imperial dogs sniffing around in our business. Need to put an end to that, don't we?
[S] Secondly, we got more of 'em hiding in a village, using the local populace as shields. Not to worry. We can dispatch them without harming the locals.
[S] Secondly, they've laid claim to another village for the empire. We're going to reclaim it for the people of Skyrim.
[S] Secondly, I need to cripple rebel production capabilities with a little sabotage.
[S] Next problem - imperial thieves have, yet again, stolen an important resource. So we're gonna take it from them permanently - by destroying it.
[S] Soldiers win wars, but where to put them is the key. We have word of an enemy courier in the area. We aim to confiscate his documents.
[S] And then, it seems an imperial worm wiggles it way back home, carrying information stolen from us. We need to steal it back.
[S] And perhaps more importantly, we've got a rescue mission lined up to break one of our boys out of a rebel controlled fort.
[S] The other bit of joy to deal with is a brother rotting in an imperial prison. He won't languish in there long, will he now?
[S] And we have an opportunity to slay the rebel field commander. Without a clear command structure, they should fall into confusion and disarray.
[S] We also have an opportunity to slay the enemy field commander. That'll put fear and confusion into those faithless dogs.
[S] And we understand a rebel garrison is close to abandoning the resistance. We need to send them a little encouragement.
[S] And we hear a bunch of imperials have found their hearts and want to join the Stormcloaks. We just need to send them a little encouragement.
[S] Next, I need someone to do a little investigating, and confirm the possibility of blackmailing the Jarl's Steward.
[S] Next, I need someone to sneak around for dirt on the Jarl's Steward. Heard there's blackmail potential there.
[S] And then there's a tiny problem with a giant that's been raiding our supply caravans... You heard me right. A giant. Need to put a stop to that.
[S] And then there's a tiny problem with a giant attacking our supply caravans. A giant! Shor's beard! As if I didn't have enough to deal with.
[S] I also would really like to get a handle on the rebel plans. I need someone to slip into their headquarters and steal their war plans.
[S] Also, I need someone to slip into the imperial headquarters and lift some documents detailing their plans. I need to know what to concentrate on.
[S] Then there's a little matter of some recruiting. I have someone in mind I'd like to join our campaign.
[S] I need to send someone out to do a little recruiting. There's someone in particular I'd like to join us.
[S] And then there's this Orc who's been hanging around causing me headaches. Something about a vision quest he needs help with.
[S] And as if that wasn't enough. I got this damn Orc hanging around, getting in the way, yapping about needing help with some kind of vision quest.

Cell.Text: [S] Excellent. I can move more soldiers through the area now that I know those scouts are dead.
[S] Good job! With those imperial scouts out of the way, I can be more aggressive about where I send our men.
[S] <<Shared>> Good work, soldier. I'll dispatch additional men to garrison the settlement.
[S] <<Shared>> You gave those mongrels a real whipping, eh? Good work. We'll be sure to send a garrison to reinforce the area and keep the peace.
[S] <<Shared>> Excellent! We've hit 'em where it hurts. Repairs will be needed when we take over, but at least the Stormcloaks won't benefit in the meantime.
[S] <<Shared>> We hit 'em where it hurts. As soon as we can, we'll take over - make the needed repairs. In the meantime, the people no longer slave for the Empire.
[S] <<Shared>> You made it! I'm impressed. It was a gamble, but I'm not about to let one of my men rot in an rebel prison.
[S] <<Shared>> Talos be praised! It was a gamble - but as Talos keeps us, we keep each other. You've done your brother well.
[S] Good. They'll think twice before crossing us while their command structure is in disarray. I hope he died well.
[S] I pray Talos overlooks our less than honorable approach. But he knows our purpose is just and true. I'm glad you made it out alive.
[S] Good work. This was a double victory. We took a garrison away from the Stormcloaks and further proved the hollowness of their cause.
[S] Excellent. That's one less settlement in imperial hands, and one more sign to all that our cause is true.
[S] Good. It seems the Ulfric's popularity is waning. His friends are turning against him. The Steward will make a powerful if untrustworthy ally.

[S] Excellent. Blackmail doesn't make for the most trusted of allies... but if we're careful, we should be able to take advantage of the situation. | Those imperials have no sense of honor. They'd sell their own mother into slavery if it paid well enough.
[S] Good job. The more citizens that join the fight against the rebels, the sooner they will see the futility of their rebellion.
[S] We grow that much stronger with each son and daughter of Skyrim who joins us. Down with the Emperor!
[S] Thanks for taking care of that. I don't think that will be the last we see of that orc. It's always good to gain potential allies.
[S] Thanks for dealing with that orc. Something tells me that's not the last time we'll see him. And, something tells me that might not be a bad thing.
[S] Good job! I knew I gave the mission to the right person.
[S] Good job! Ulfric was right about you. I'm glad to have you with us!
